Number Guessing Game
The Number Guessing Game is a simple Java Swing-based guessing game where the player has to guess a randomly generated number within a specified range. The game provides the option to set the number of attempts for each round and offers a "hint" option to reveal the last digit of the target number.

How to Play
Getting Started

To play the Number Guessing Game, make sure you have Java and Eclipse IDE installed on your computer.

Clone the Repository

Clone this repository to your local machine using the following command:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/NumberGuessingGame.git
Import Project into Eclipse

Open Eclipse IDE and choose "File" > "Import."
Select "Existing Projects into Workspace" and click "Next."
Browse to the cloned repository directory and select the project (NumberGuessingGame).
Click "Finish" to import the project into Eclipse.
Run the Game

Open the NumberGuessingGame.java file in the Number_Game package.
Right-click on the code and select "Run As" > "Java Application."
The GUI for the Number Guessing Game will appear.
Game Instructions

Enter the desired number of attempts for each round in the provided text field.
Click the "Start Game" button to begin a round.
The game will generate a random number between 1 and 100, and you have to guess the number within the given attempts.
When prompted, enter your guess in the input dialog. You can also type "hint" to get a clue about the last digit of the target number.
After each round, you will receive feedback on whether your guess is too low, too high, or correct.
The game will keep track of your score based on the number of successful rounds.
You can choose to play again after each round, or you can exit the game.
Enjoy the Game

Have fun playing the Number Guessing Game and challenge yourself to improve your guessing skills!

